    <content>&lt;b&gt;American Economic Review&lt;/b&gt; &lt;br&gt;We empirically characterize how China is internationalizing its bond market by staggering the entry of different types of foreign investors into its domestic market and propose a dynamic reputation model to explain this strategy. Our framework rationalizes China’s strategy as trying to build credibility as a safe issuer while reducing the cost of capital flight. We use our framework to shed light on China’s response to episodes of capital outflows. (JEL E44, F38, G12, G15, G23, O16, P34)</content>
    <link href="https://doi.org/10.1257/aer.20221722"/>
